<a href="javascript:;" class="show-all" id="showMore">
<em>展开全文</em>
</a>
</section>
</div>
<div class="hidden-content control-hide">
<p>Apart from doing exercise, there are also other essential factors contributing to a healthy lifestyle. The first to be mentioned is a balanced diet. A popular saying, which goes "you are what you eat" fully illustrates the importance of the food we take. Next comes dealing with our stress level properly. While mental health is often neglected by us, it can cause vital disruptions in our life. Therefore, as long as we take measures to look after our body and mind, I am confident that most of us will achieve a healthy lifestyle. </p>
<p><strong>亲子关系紧张以及如何缓解</strong></p>
<p>题目:the importance of parents-children relationship and how to handle it </p>
<p>开头段: </p>
<p>As one of the most important relationships in human society. the relationship between parents and children has become a social concern in the past few decades. it goes without questioning that the above mentioned relationship serves a vital role in our society. </p>
<p>中间段(importance ): </p>
<p>First of all. Children from a stable and loving family are more likely to contribute more to their country and society. A stress-free home allows children to concentrate completely on their personal development, which often leads to great achievements later on.Secondly. it is generally agreed that harmonious families can lead to a lower crime rate in the long term. According to statistics of the past few decades.a great number of criminals suffered from damaging family relationships in their childhood. </p>
<p>结尾段: </p>
<p>Needless to say, it is beneficial to all if the parents-children relationship could be handled well. My suggestions are listed as follows. The first one is constructive conversation. To focus on the actual problem with a calm discussion serves as a more effective solution than having pointless arguments Secondly, mutual understanding is also required from both sides. It's better if parents could realize how they used to behave at their children's age, while children should recognize their parents selfless love.To conclude from the above, it takes a collective effort, which includes standing in each others’ shoes and communicating calmly. to achieve for long and all. </p>
<p><strong>环境保护/垃圾分类的重要性</strong></p>
<p>题目:the importance of waste/rubbish classification and how to encourage it </p>
<p>开头段: </p>
<p>With the rapid development of economy and society,recent years have seen a growing tendency of waste classification in many big cities in China.(解释谚语) </p>
<p>中间段(importance): </p>
<p>It goes without questioning that the importance of waste classification should be recognized by all citizens. To start with, waste classification serves a key role in environment protection.It is universally acknowledged that certain types of waste. such as plastic bags.can do great harm to our environment. Secondly. energy saving. which is a social concern. also relies on proper waste classification. </p>
<p>结尾段(how to): </p>
<p>The other issue faced by the whole society is how to reinforce the waste classification regulations. My suggestions are listed in this paragraph. On the one hand, it is critical that our government introduces regulations in a more educated way which allows people who are not familiar with the idea to gradually get used to it. On the other hand, people should remind each other to strictly follow the regulations. especially in crowded areas. To conclude from the above, waste classification. whose importance is doubtless. requires a joint effort from everybody living in the city. </p>
<p>写作必备谚语</p>
<p>1：Actions speak louder than words.事实胜于雄辩</p>
<p>2：All is not gold that glitters.发光的未必都是金子</p>
<p>3：All roads lead to Rome.条条大路通罗马</p>
<p>4：A good beginning is half done.良好的开端是成功的一半</p>
<p>5：Every advantage has its disadvantage有利必有弊</p>
<p>6：A miss is as good as a mile.失之毫厘，差之千里</p>
<p>7：Failure is the mother of success.失败是成功之母</p>
<p>8：Industry is the parent of success.勤奋是成功之母</p>
<p>9：It is never too old to learn.活到老，学到老</p>
<p>10：Knowledge is power.知识就是力量</p>
<p>11：Nothing in the world is difficult for one who sets his mind to it.世上无难事，只怕有心人。</p>
